<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Consul at Hanoi (
                        Gibson
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v07p1</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d16</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">16</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-04-02T01:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-04-02T01:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-02T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-02T01:00:00-05:00" n="16" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d16">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851<gloss target="#t_G1">G</gloss>.01/4–249:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Hanoi</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanoi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-02T14:00:00+08:00">April 2, 1949—2 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. Vietminh radio made following announcement: “The High Command of the
                    Vietnamese resistance forces (NB Vietminh) announces that the first elements of
                    the Chinese forces of liberation<note n="1" xml:id="d16fn1">Chinese Communist
                        forces under Mao Tse-tung.</note> have registered great activity recently at
                    the Sino-Vietnamese frontier.” Radio then referred to “important support which
                    the Vietnam forces have received as a result.”</p>
                <pb facs="0032" n="18" xml:id="pg_18"/>
                <p>This is first official acknowledgment by Vietminh of military cooperation with
                    Chinese.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, repeated Paris 5, pouched Saigon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
